The article is about a speech given by Dr. Jill Biden, the First Lady of the United States, at a conference in Alexandria, VA. In her speech, she emphasizes the importance of supporting military spouses and their families. She discusses the initiatives taken by the government to address the employment challenges faced by military spouses, such as executive orders to make it easier for spouses to find jobs and access child care. Dr. Biden also calls on employers to continue hiring and retaining military spouses and encourages businesses to join the Military Spouse Employment Partnership. She expresses gratitude to all those who have supported military families and assures them that the government will continue to find ways to support them.